For running the ant based release utilities successfully, you will need to have

- an ANT installation (at least 1.6)
- all projects downloaded from SVN

To create a new release of leJOS NXT, please perform the following steps:

1. Open a shell (on Windows, you will need a cygwin shell) and change directory to $LEJOS_HOME/release
2. Ensure you have the latest VM and jar files built. The release build file does not rebuild them.
3. Set the correct version number in release/build.properties
4. On Windows, make sure you have runjava.exe in snapshot/bin.
5. Run "ant"
6. After the ant script has finished (including, the packed distributions for Linux and Windows may be found at $LEJOS_HOME/release/dist
